issue.title: [CF 1601] Rake's Stun Causing Icon to Show Outside of Conditions
issue.body:
This happens a little less than half the time.  The three Rake icons I have set up are set to show when 1) Rake debuff is absent on the target. 2) Rake debuff exists on target with less than 5 seconds left on said debuff and 2 stacks of Bloodtalons on the player. 3) One stack of rake on target that has less than 3.3 seconds left.

 

When I stealth Rake a fresh mob, the conditions should allow for the next icon in the priority to show.  But sometimes, Rake's stun (which creates a second Rake icon on the target) will keep Rake showing on the Meta until the stun falls off.  I've tried to recreate this on the dummy, but was unsuccessful although the stun still shows.  It may only be relevant to mobs.
